OL,3,CGrant Shapps refuses to commit to 3%
OL,4,Cdefence spending in election manifesto
OL,6,FHe has been under increasing pressure
OL,7,Fto go beyond the government's current
OL,8,Fpledge of spending 2.5% of GDP on
OL,9,Fdefence, not least from the outgoing
OL,10,FWells MP and former Armed Forces
OL,11,FMinister, James Heappey.
OL,13,FMr Heappey, who stood down from his
OL,14,Fgovernment role last month, is among a
OL,15,Fnumber of senior Conservative MPs
OL,16,Furging Mr Shapps that the UK's armed
OL,17,Fforces "urgently" need a more
OL,18,Fsignificant budget.
