OL,3,CGrant Shapps refuses to commit to 3%
OL,4,Cdefence spending in election manifesto
OL,6,F"We're at about 2.3% so we're a long
OL,7,Fway there," he said.
OL,9,F"I should caution that our opponents,
OL,10,Fthe Labour Party, only want to spend
OL,11,F2%, the NATO minimum. That would mean
OL,12,F#7 billion slashed off our defence
OL,13,Fspending every year."
OL,15,FThe Defence Secretary was with the
OL,16,FConservative MP for Filton and Bradley
OL,17,FStoke, Jack Lopresti, on his visit to
OL,18,Fthe MoD site in South Gloucestershire.
