OL,3,CGrant Shapps refuses to commit to 3%
OL,4,Cdefence spending in election manifesto
OL,6,F"We believe in the Labour party that
OL,7,Fthe first duty of any Government is to
OL,8,Fprotect its people," Ms Hazelgrove
OL,9,Fsaid.
OL,11,F"When we were last in Government, we
OL,12,Fwere incredibly proud that we were
OL,13,Finvesting 2.5% of GDP in defence. What
OL,14,Fwe've seen in Conservatives are real
OL,15,Fcutbacks on that.
OL,17,F"We don't get to see every pound or
OL,18,Fpenny within the defence budget when
OL,19,Fyou're in opposition - you only get
OL,20,Fthat privilege in Government.
